    <abstract>
      <t>Cisco's Service-Level Assurance Protocol (Cisco's SLA Protocol) is a Performance Measurement protocol that has been widely deployed.  The protocol is used to measure service-level parameters such as network latency, delay variation, and packet/frame loss.  This document describes the Cisco SLA Protocol Measurement-Type UDP-Measurement, to enable vendor interoperability.  This document is not an Internet Standards Track specification; it is published for informational purposes.</t>
    </abstract>
